values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_NWM_KOTH_2
values.value:
The mutineers are trapped in an unfortified castle with low morale and dwindling supplies. Your allies have given you every possible advantage in this fight. Now is the time to strike!

Capture event-limited Seats of Power to earn points! Eastwatch-by-the-Sea, the Shadow Tower, the Nightfort, and Castle Black will unlock for short windows of time during each Hour of the Wolf round event. To help you capture these Seats of Power, special Boosts are available in the Item Exchange tab of your Inventory. While you hold one of these Seats of Power, you and any Bannermen to whom you assign titles will receive points every minute. Maintain control of your Seat of Power for as long as possible to earn maximum points!
Part of the 'Night's Watch Mutiny' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_CRAFT_1
values.value:
To earn a name for himself other than Snow, Jon leaves home to join his uncle, Benjen Stark, among the Night's Watch. Expecting to find the proud military order he grew up hearing stories of, he instead finds a group of thieves, cutthroats, and worse. Among the miserable lot, however, Jon finds unlikely allies who may have more to offer than they first appear.

Craft any event gear to earn points! Northern Fox Pelts materials for the Northern Noble gear set are available in other As The Crow Flies events. 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_CRAFT_2
values.value:
Though he aspires to be a ranger, Jon is made steward to Jeor Mormont, the Lord Commander of Castle Black. When a body recovered from Beyond the Wall rises in the night and attacks the Lord Commander, Jon acts and saves his life. In gratitude, Mormont bestows him with the Valyrian steel sword, Longclaw-- an heirloom deemed more worthy in Jon's hands; it's pommel reshaped from a bear's head to a wolf's.

Craft any Trinket to earn points! Earn materials for the Mormont Pommel Trinket by defeating creatures in the You Knelt As Boys event. 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_PVE_1
values.value:
Bastard or not, Jon's upbringing gave him experience and skill with arms. Among the many recruits of the Night's Watch, few had ever learned to hold a blade, let alone how to avoid getting killed by one. One such recruit, Samwell Tarly, needs more help than most to stay on his feet-- if these trainees are to be the shield that guards the realms of men, it falls to Jon to lend his expertise.

Defeat Night's Watch Trainees to earn points! 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_PVE_2
values.value:
Having shown their mettle, Jon and his fellow recruits are to be accepted as full brothers of the Night's Watch. While others have chosen to take their vows in Castle Black's sept, Jon has chosen the lone Wierwood tree beyond the Wall. Accompanied by Sam and Ghost, Jon utters the most important words of his life and is welcomed with open arms to the Brotherhood. 

Defeat any non-event creature on the map to earn points! While this event is active, non-event creatures drop materials for the new Mormont Pommel trinket, which can be crafted for points in the A commander in the making! event. 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_PVE_RALLY_1
values.value:
Dark wings, dark words—Lord Eddard Stark has been executed by the Lannisters. With all haste, Jon rides off to meet his brother Robb and march south to war... but his oath requires he stay or be executed. His brothers in black ride after him, pleading he reconsider. Yet it is in the recitation of their oath that Jon accepts the true weight of his vow, and with a solemn heart, returns home to Castle Black

Defeat Night's Watch Master-At-Arms to earn points! 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_TRADE_1
values.value:
Proud and sure of himself after besting the other recruits, Jon entreats with his uncle Benjen to allow him north of the wall, certain that he's ready. Yet Benjen humbles him, and reminds Jon that though he may be more skilled than his peers, he is still but a boy-- unprepared for the dangers that lurk beyond the Wall

Braavosi Loan trophy recipes are available while this event is active. Exchange Braavosi Loan trophies in the Recipes tab of your Inventory to earn points! 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_TRADE_2
values.value:
With Benjen Stark missing, Jon joins the Lord Commander's march Beyond the Wall in hopes of finding him.Jon's strength and conviction have already been tested, but now he must face dangers far greater than any before. He knows nothing of what lies beyond the wall...

Exchange Braavosi Loan trophies in the Recipes tab of your Inventory to earn points. This event's Recipes are your last chance to use Braavosi Loan trophies before they are converted into Trader's Scrip! 
Part of the 'As Crow Flies' Event

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_SNOW1_UMBRELLA_1
values.value:
A bastard looks upon his home one last time. He's said his farewells to those he loves and to the life he knew before. The biting wind does little to impede him or the direwolf at his side; his hopes of finding a place where they can both belong drive him onward. Though he cannot hear the drums of war, they echo farther north than he has ever dreamt of going.

Look for these Featured Rewards throughout the As The Crow Flies event:
* Northern Fox Pelts are used to craft the Northern Noble gear set!
* Mormont Pommel Silver Alloy are used to craft the Mormont Pommel trinket!
* Braavosi Loan trophies can be traded for prizes in the Recipes tab of your Inventory while the First Ranger or Bastard Beyond the Wall events are active. Remember to use all your Braavosi Loan trophies before the Bastard Beyond the Wall event ends!

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_STANDALONE_TRINFECTA2_PVE_1
values.value:
A single well-placed strike can turn the tide of battle. Know your enemy's weakness and exploit it.

Defeat any non-event creature on the map to earn points! While this event is active, non-event creatures drop materials for trinkets, which can be crafted for points in the Three-Eyed Raven: Intuition II event. Materials earned come from the following Trinket Collections:

House Manderly, Valyrian Dragon, House Baratheon, Artifacts of R'hllor,  House Whent Heirlooms

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_TESTYOURMETTLE_1
values.value: In the throes of battle, a legend is born! From the most unlikely of contenders, a Lord can ascend to the summit of power and glory. For a 24 hours, they put everything on the line against rival Lords, risking their name for the promise of glory, and perhaps even infamy. The opportunity is yours to seize, to enter the crucible and test your mettle against other mighty Lords from other kingdoms. Journey forth and claim a Seat of Power, defend it with all your might, and inscribe your name in the annals of history. At the end, your actions will judge your valor by how long your capable of holding onto a Seat of Power. But beware, others are vying for glory. Are you prepared to Test Your Mettle?

values.name: ACTIVITY_DESCRIPTION_VALENTINES_GEMS_1
values.value:
"Merchants from the Jade Sea have arrived on the shores of Westeros with abundant stores of gold!

Celebrate Valentine's Day with EVEN MORE GOLD! Using Gems to redeem bundles in the Store awards points towards this event.
If the purchases made with Gems contain Gold, that Gold will contribute to the progress of the separate Valentines Day Celebration Event. Daily Deliveries and Rewards Passes only award points for initial gold received at the time of purchase. Rewards must be collected before the promotion ends."

values.name: ANNUITY_HELP_TEXT
values.value:
Reward Passes grant rewards over time!

Each pass has a schedule of rewards. Tap on an entry in the schedule for a list of the items it contains.

After claiming a reward, you must wait some time before being able to claim the next, but you cannot miss any rewards.

values.name: ANNUITY_TUTORIAL_1
values.value:
My little birds have informed me of a new means of acquiring great things that could aid your rule, my lord.

Come with me to the Hidden Market behind the Tavern, if you would.

values.name: ANNUITY_TUTORIAL_1_F
values.value:
My little birds have informed me of a new means of acquiring great things that could aid your rule, my lady.

Come with me to the Hidden Market behind the Tavern, if you would.

values.name: ANNUITY_TUTORIAL_2
values.value:
My network can put you in contact with merchants and smugglers that can provide goods through timed contracts.

With some diligence and patience, these trade contracts can be quite enriching.

values.name: ANNUITY_TUTORIAL_3
values.value:
We can arrange "Reward Pass" contracts with merchants. We provide them with payment up front, and we can call upon them to provide various rewards over time.

After claiming a reward, we must wait for some time before they are able to provide the next, but over time you are guaranteed all of the promised goods.

values.name: ANNUITY_TUTORIAL_4
values.value:
We can arrange for "Daily Deliveries" from smugglers and the like. They will provide identical shipments at a steady rate, typically once a day, but be sure to claim them before the next delivery arrives.

They will happily redistribute any unclaimed goods to themselves if given half a chance.

values.name: ANNUITY_TUTORIAL_5
values.value: Watch for opportunities for these contracts amongst the Special and Featured Offers.

values.name: CARAVAN_BANDITS_BRICK_DESC
values.value: A highwayman standing guard over a poorly-hidden cache of bricks. Why stand out in the cold staring at a pile of bricks? Who knows, but no good can come of it.

values.name: CARAVAN_MERCENARIES_FRAGMENTS_DESC
values.value: A sellsword dragging a heavy cart full of books, looking equal parts confused and furious. Perhaps you could lighten their burden?

values.name: CARAVAN_MILITANTS_PALE_STEEL_DESC
values.value: A deserter from the Westerlands, still clad in their fine stolen armor. Perhaps your Maester could repurpose some of that excellent steel…

values.name: CARAVAN_TRIBESMEN_SOLDIER_PINE_DESC
values.value: A civilian wagon besieged by angry Moon Brothers! Drive off the hill tribesmen to bring your woodcutters — and the soldier pine they carry — safely home.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_ARC_WINTERISHERE_1
values.value: Everyone you know will die before winter is over if we don't defeat the Enemy to the north.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_ARC_WINTERISHERE_2
values.value: This isn't about living in harmony; it's just about living.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_ARC_WINTERISHERE_3
values.value: Ice, a wall of ice. The Wall… it's where the Wall meets the sea.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_ARC_WINTERISHERE_4
values.value: There's a castle there. There's a mountain, looks like an arrowhead.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_ARC_WINTERISHERE_5
values.value: The dead are marching past... thousands of them…

values.name: CharacterText_TutorialDragonAdvancement_1
values.value: "Zaldrīzes buzdari iksos daor" — a dragon is not a slave. It will not obey a whip. Chains and walls will stunt its growth.

values.name: CharacterText_TutorialDragonAdvancement_2
values.value: If you want your dragon to flourish you must respect its strength, give it space to grow, and above all, feed it well.

values.name: CharacterText_TutorialDragonAdvancement_3
values.value: Right now your dragon only needs the fire's warmth, but soon it will require meat. A few carcasses a day will sate its hunger.

values.name: CharacterText_TutorialDragonAdvancement_4
values.value: Your dragon's appetite is limited, so make the most of your feedings with better Livestock. Bonus Feed items will tempt a satisfied dragon to eat more.

values.name: CharacterText_TutorialDragonAdvancement_5
values.value: Tend your dragon well through its early stages and it will grow into a fearsome ally, like Balerion the Dread and the great dragons of old.

values.name: CharacterText_TutorialDragonIntro_1
values.value: How strange… this ruin is built in the Old Valyrian style. I suggest you excavate immediately. My ancestors had many secrets worth uncovering.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONMARCH_1
values.value: Your dragon is ready to stretch its wings. It is still too young and unruly to join a rally or besiege a castle, but it can assist with simple hunts.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONMARCH_2
values.value: Be warned, your dragon cannot defend your Keep while it is away. It can be wounded or incapacitated by combat, but mortal weapons cannot kill it.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONMARCH_FIREBREATH_1
values.value: If you have charges available when you begin a march, you can command your dragon to attack with Fire Breath.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONMARCH_FIREBREATH_2
values.value: Your dragon will begin the battle with a devastating rain of fire, damaging the enemy before they have a chance to react.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONRESEARCH_1
values.value: Centuries ago the Doom of Valyria nearly erased dragons from the world, and all we had learned about them went up in flames… or so we thought.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONRESEARCH_2
values.value: Send your Maesters to uncover the lost dragon lore of Old Valyria. Some of their wisdom must survive, and you will need it to raise your dragon well.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONRESEARCH_FIREBREATH_1
values.value: Your dragon is now ready to unleash its Fire Breath! This terrifying attack weakens the enemy before a battle begins.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONRESEARCH_FIREBREATH_2
values.value: Attacking with Fire Breath is exhausting. You must recharge your dragon's flame with Fire Stones each time it uses the ability.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONTALENTS_1
values.value: Some Maesters claim dragons are more intelligent than men — a claim I can easily believe. Your dragon will become even more talented as it grows.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONTALENTS_2
values.value: Dragons cannot excel in all areas at once. Help your dragon focus on talents that suit your needs in the moment. When your needs change, your dragon will adapt.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIALDRAGONTALENTS_3
values.value: This versatility is your dragon's most powerful weapon. Scout ahead and think strategically to make the most of its skills.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIAL_DAILIES_INTRO_1
values.value: Lofty goals are well and good, but you must also remember to manage the day-to-day operations of your Keep.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIAL_DAILIES_INTRO_2
values.value: The Daily Quests ledger lists your everyday duties as lord of this Keep. Efficiency is its own reward… but of course, I will also reward you myself.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIAL_DAILIES_INTRO_2_F
values.value: The Daily Quests ledger lists your everyday duties as lady of this Keep. Efficiency is its own reward… but of course, I will also reward you myself.

values.name: CHARACTERTEXT_TUTORIAL_DAILIES_INTRO_3
values.value: Each day, some quests will be more urgent or profitable than others. I will make special note of them, so remember to check the ledger regularly.

values.name: DRAGON_DIALOG_NO_HUNGER_ITEMS_DESC
values.value: Bonus Feed items allow you to continue feeding your dragon beyond the normal daily allotment. Keep an eye out for Bonus Feed items in event rewards and special offers!

values.name: DRAGON_GET_MORE_HUNGER_ITEMS_BODY
values.value: You can feed your dragon beyond the daily limit by using Bonus Feed items. Bonus Feed items can be acquired in the following ways:

values.name: DRAGON_INFO_BODY3
values.value: The first time you feed your dragon each day, you will gain a temporary bonus to experience gained from feeding. This bonus increases every day up to a maximum, and resets to +0% after every 10 levels your dragon gains.

values.name: DRAGON_INFO_EQUIPMENT_PARAGRAPH_5
values.value:
In addition to 3 gear slots for the Dragon Gear, you can gain access to an additional trinket slot. This slot is unlocked by researching the node on the new research tree, Dragon Care.

This trinket slot allows players to equip an additional trinket from their equipment list to further empower their kingdom and army.

values.name: DRAGON_INFO_TRAINING_PARAGRAPH_1
values.value:
The Dragon Pit houses your fearsome dragon. Visit regularly to feed your dragon, help it grow, train it to accompany your armies, equip it with armor to strengthen your army, and study lost histories to 
unlock its full potential. When your dragon is wounded, it will rest here until healed.

values.name: DRAGON_INFO_TREES_PARAGRAPH_2
values.value:
The dragon Research trees allow you to strengthen your dragon and their influence on your troops, your keep’s defense, resource gathering, and overall power.

There are 6 research trees to study, those are:
* Nurturing
* Hatchling
* Whelp
* Adolescent
* Adult
* Dragon Care

As you level up your dragon, more research trees will become available. With the addition of dragon Gear, the new Dragon Care tree will allow you to further strengthen your dragon and give you access to a second trinket slot.

values.name: DRAGON_MAX_LEVEL_BODY
values.value: Adult dragons are powerful magical creatures, breathing fire to damage enemy troops directly. Adults can also rally with allied armies, reinforce Keeps, and are brave enough to attack Seats of Power.

values.name: DRAGON_MAX_LEVEL_TITLE
values.value: Max Level Reached! Coming soon: Adult Dragons

values.name: DRAGON_PHASEPREVIEW_ADOLESCENT
values.value: Adolescent dragons can learn the powerful defensive combat ability Repel Strike (research unlocks LV 27), and eventually grow strong enough to attack enemy Keeps (research unlocks LV 31). Beginning at this phase, the appearance of the dragon's horns can be customized.

values.name: DRAGON_PHASEPREVIEW_ADULT
values.value: Adult dragons can learn to attack with their fire breath (research unlocks LV 40), and are mature enough to join Rallies (research unlocks LV 41) and attack Seats of Power (research unlocks LV 41).

values.name: DRAGON_PHASEPREVIEW_HATCHLING
values.value: Hatchlings can learn to bravely defend your city in combat (research unlocks LV 6). Once the dragon has hatched, its eye color can be customized.

values.name: DRAGON_PHASEPREVIEW_HATCHLING_A
values.value: Hatchlings can learn to attack Creatures (research unlocks LV 6). Once the dragon has hatched, its eye color can be customized.

values.name: DRAGON_PHASEPREVIEW_WHELP
values.value: Whelps can learn to attack Creatures (research unlocks LV 12) and gather Resources (research unlocks LV 13+) alongside your armies.

values.name: DRAGON_PHASEPREVIEW_WHELP_A
values.value: Whelps can learn to bravely defend your city in combat (research unlocks LV 12) and gather Resources (research unlocks LV 13+) alongside your armies.

values.name: EXPEDITION_DESCRIPTION_MASTEROFWAR_FIELDOFFIRE
values.value: Perhaps no one in history understood the strategic use of dragons better than Rhaenys, Visenya, and Aegon Targaryen. At the height of the War of Conquest, Aegon and his sisters met the combined Gardener-Lannister army on an open field of dry grain. Instead of using their dragons to attack directly, the Targaryens set fire to the field itself, encircling the enemy in an inescapable wall of flame.

values.name: EXPEDITION_DESCRIPTION_MASTEROFWAR_GODSEYE
values.value: Old age weakens men, but dragons only grow stronger with time. In 42 AC, Prince Aegon Targaryen challenged King Maegor the Cruel for control of the Iron Throne. Both were dragonriders, but Maegor had inherited Balerion the Dread, legendary companion of Aegon the Conqueror. Prince Aegon's Quicksilver was no match for the larger, stronger dragon — Balerion ripped Quicksilver's wing from her body mid-flight.

values.name: EXPEDITION_DESCRIPTION_MASTEROFWAR_HARRENHAL
values.value: When King Harren Hoare defied Aegon the Conqueror, he learned that even the greatest stronghold is of little use against a dragon. Harrenhal's stone walls were built too high and thick for any siege engine to topple, but Balerion the Dread simply flew over the walls and unleashed fire on the stone towers until they glowed red-hot, roasting King Harren alive.

values.name: EXPEDITION_DESCRIPTION_MASTEROFWAR_HELLHOLT
values.value: Spears and arrows are no match for a dragon's scales, but there is one weakness in their armor. As Queen Rhaenys and her dragon Meraxes fought to subdue the Dornish castle Hellholt during the First Dornish War, a lucky scorpion bolt caught Meraxes in the eye, piercing through her skull. The dragon lost her rider and destroyed half of Hellholt as she plummeted to the ground, starting King Aegon on a two-year campaign of vengeance known as the Dragon's Wroth.

values.name: EXPEDITION_DESCRIPTION_MASTEROFWAR_PRINCESPASS
values.value: Sometimes, the most effective tactic against dragons is not to do battle at all. During Aegon's War of Conquest and the Dornish Wars that followed, the Dornish simply abandoned their castles and settlements whenever a dragonrider approached. With nothing of value to attack, the dragons would leave — whereupon Dornish spearmen returned to dispatch whatever stewards or garrisons the enemy had left behind.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_SCRIP_1_DESC
values.value: A merchant's promise to repay a debt. Trophies can be converted into Trader's Scrip after their event ends; Scrip can then be exchanged for goods in the Recipes tab of your Inventory.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_BARATHEON_1_DESC
values.value:
A fallen ruby from a gallant warrior's armor, nearly lost in the rushing waters of the Trident.

Can be used in Recipes during the Robert's Rebellion event, or converted to Trader's Scrip when the event ends. 
Part of the 'Robert's Rebellion' Event

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_BROTHERS_1_DESC
values.value:
House Clegane's sigil is three black dogs on a yellow field. To many in Westeros, these banners herald destruction and death. To the Brotherhood, they are a mark of a job well done.

Can be used in Recipes during the Brotherhood Without Banners event, or converted to Trader's Scrip when the event ends. 
Part of the 'Brotherhood Without Banners' Event

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_CONQUEROR_1_DESC
values.value:
"All of you were torn from your mothers' arms and raised as slaves. Now, you are liberators!"

Can be used in Recipes during the Mother of Dragons event, or converted to Trader's Scrip when the event ends.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_CONQUEST_1_DESC
values.value:
The Great Houses Gardener, Hoare, and Durrandon all fell before the might of Aegon the Conqueror.

Can be used in Recipes during the Aegon's Conquest event, or converted to Trader's Scrip once the event ends.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_DRAGONPAST_1_DESC
values.value:
The melted remnants of an unnamed soldier's armor, ordered to face a dragon in a hellish assault.

Can be used in Recipes during the Dragons of the Past event, or converted to Trader's Scrip when the event ends. 
Part of the 'Dragons of the Past' Event

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_FALCONKNIGHT_1_DESC
values.value:
Relics inscribed with the Old Tongue of the First Men.

Can be used in Recipes during the Knights of the Vale event, or converted to Trader's Scrip when the event ends.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_FOUNDATIONS_1_DESC
values.value:
A wheel from a commandeered supply line.

Can be used in Recipes during the Foundations - Bran the Builder event, or converted to Trader's Scrip when the event ends.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_GREATHUNT_1_DESC
values.value:
A memento of a successful hunt.

Can be used in Recipes during the Great Hunt event, or converted to Trader's Scrip once the event ends.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_HARRENHAL_1_DESC
values.value:
Delicate petals from a rare flower, blue as winter frost.

Can be used in Recipes during the Tourney at Harrenhal event, or converted to Trader's Scrip once the event ends.

values.name: ITEM_EVENT_TROPHY_KINGSGUARD_1_DESC

values.value:
This event features a Milestone Challenge. Your progress is based on the highest milestone you reach in the event. When you achieve a higher milestone than you have before you receive the cumulative rewards for all milestones between your previous highest and your new highest milestone.

You can preview the cumulative rewards for reaching a particular milestone by adjusting the slider and tapping the chest. As you reach higher milestones, still higher challenge milestones and their associated rewards may be revealed.

Leaderboards accompanying a Milestone Challenge can still be based on accumulated points. View the Event Points for more information.

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_CATEGORY_THEDEAD_DESC
values.value:
This creature is considered one of "the Dead". Bonuses which are "vs. the Dead" benefit you when fighting this creature.

"They're death. You can't beat death!"

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_CATEGORY_WORLDBOSS_DESC
values.value:
This creature is a World Boss. Bonuses which are "vs. World Boss" benefit you when fighting this creature. Every combat victory against a World Boss lowers its health. When the World Boss's health is fully depleted it will return at a higher level, offering a greater challenge and better rewards.

"Are you afraid? Good. You’re in the great game now, and the great game’s terrifying."

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_COMBAT_ELITE_DESC
values.value:
Elite Creatures must be defeated multiple times. Each victory reduces its health and it is defeated when its health is fully depleted.

They are typically more difficult than a normal creature of the same level.

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_COMBAT_RALLY_DESC
values.value:
Rally Creatures must be attacked in a rally of two or more players in the same allegiance.

They are typically more difficult than a normal creature of the same level.

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_REWARDBEHAVIOR_ELITE_ALLEGIANCEFINAL_DESC
values.value: On its final defeat, this Elite sends a reward to every member of the victorious allegiance.

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_REWARDBEHAVIOR_ELITE_GREATERFINAL_BOUNTY_DESC
values.value:
This Elite drops Bounties on its final defeat.

Bounties can be crafted into Instant Boosts via Inventory: Recipes.

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_REWARDBEHAVIOR_ELITE_GREATERFINAL_DESC

values.name: MONSTER_BADGE_REWARDS_CARAVAN_BRICK_DESC

Bricks are required to upgrade most buildings.

values.value: 'A bear there was, a bear, a bear! All black and brown, and covered with hair.' - The Bear and the Maiden Fair

values.name: MONSTER_BLACKFYRE_COMMANDER_DESC

values.name: MONSTER_BLACKFYRE_RANGED_DESC
values.value: In 258 AC, Maelys the Monstrous united an army of sellswords, corsairs, and exiles under the banner of House Blackfyre.

values.name: MONSTER_BOAR_DESC
values.value: Many a great person has been killed by a charging boar… More wine?

values.name: MONSTER_BOLTON_CAVALRY_DESC
values.value: As loyal and vicious as a pack of hounds, the last of the Bolton bannermen refuse to accept the ancient house's demise.

values.name: MONSTER_BOLTON_COMMANDER_DESC
values.value: As loyal and vicious as a pack of hounds, the Bolton army is renowned for their cruelty.

values.name: MONSTER_BRIGAND_DESC
values.value: An army comprised of mostly infantry.

values.name: MONSTER_BROTHERHOOD_BANNERS_DESC
values.value: A soldier of the Brotherhood Without Banners is as much a farce as any knight with a fancy banner. Put out their flame with your steel.

values.name: MONSTER_CAVE_DESC
values.value: A deep cavern guarded by hired blades. Who knows what treasures — or what dangers — lie within?

values.name: MONSTER_CIAL_BOLTON_RANGED_DESC
values.value: As loyal and vicious as a pack of hounds, the Bolton army is renowned for their cruelty.

values.name: MONSTER_CLEGANE_COMMANDER_DESC
values.value: A fetching price was put on the head of the Mountain and his bannermen after their violent raids in the Riverlands. Go and claim it.

values.name: MONSTER_CLEGANE_INFANTRY_DESC
values.value: House Clegane was built upon dead children. When Lannister forces stormed the Red Keep, Gregor Clegane was found with the Targaryen heirs laid beside the Iron Throne. Bring justice to the realm and defeat any Clegane Bannerman on sight.

values.name: MONSTER_CONQUEST3_CAVALRY_ELITE_DESC
values.value: Storm King Argilac dared to insult Aegon the Conqueror, and he paid the price for his arrogance. Only his house’s banner lives on — Orys Baratheon, Aegon's Hand of the King, adopted the stag sigil after he conquered Storm’s End in Aegon’s name.

values.name: MONSTER_CONQUEST3_COMMANDER_ELITE_RALLY_DESC
values.value: Thanks to the Reach’s plentiful food, King Mern Gardener commanded the largest army in Westeros. Unfortunately, that just made Aegon’s victory at the Field of Fire more impressive, and more devastating.

values.name: MONSTER_CONQUEST3_INFANTRY_ELITE_DESC
values.value: Even in the time of Aegon’s Conquest, Lannister wealth was legendary. Still, all the gold in the Kingdom of the Rock couldn’t buy victory against Aegon’s dragons.

values.name: MONSTER_CONQUEST3_RANGED_ELITE_DESC
values.value: The Ironborn of House Hoare plundered the Riverlands for decades to build a legacy for King Harren the Black — the hulking fortress of Harrenhal. When Harren defied Aegon the Conqueror, that fortress became their tomb.

values.name: MONSTER_DIRE_WOLF_DESC
values.value: The Direwolf is the sigil of House Stark, larger than a typical wolf, and rarely found south of the Wall. What could have brought it here?

values.name: MONSTER_DIRE_WOLF_ELITE_DESC
values.value: The Direwolf is the sigil of House Stark, larger than a typical wolf, and rarely found south of the Wall. What could have brought it here?

values.name: MONSTER_DOTHRAKI_DESC
values.value: They may not gleam like Westerosi knights, but the Dothraki are some of the most fearsome warriors in the world. Underestimate them at your peril.

values.name: MONSTER_DRAGONRIDER_DESC
values.value: Those who ride dragons fear little, for they seek to tame the sky itself. Engulfed by flame, rent by gnashing teeth, or gutted by sharp claws, a dragon's enemies know no peace.

values.name: MONSTER_ELK_DESC
values.value: A hunter's skill is measured by the size of the beasts they fell. Taking a trophy from an elk this massive would surely increase your renown!

values.name: MONSTER_ESSOSPIRATE_DESC

values.name: MONSTER_FACELESS_RANGEDELITE_DESC

values.value:
Today you begin your rise to power as a noble of Westeros! 

As head of your House, navigate the dangerous political landscape of Westeros. Forge strategic alliances and outmaneuver rival threats to amass the might and resources necessary to capture iconic Seats of Power -- and ultimately the Iron Throne.  

At present, only Seats of Power in the North are available for capture. In the coming weeks, more regions will become available for conquest. The Kingdom Map is available for viewing information for each Seat of Power, whether or not it is unlocked, and its ownership status.

Thank you for playing Game of Thrones: Conquest™!

~ the Game of Thrones: Conquest™ Team

values.name: SYSTEM_MESSAGE_ STAKEYOURCLAIM_PREEVENT
values.value:
Soon, the allegiances in your kingdom, along with those in two other kingdoms, will set forth on a new adventure. You will leave your current kingdoms behind as you look for new territory to stake your claim in. 
When the event starts, owners of Seats of Power will be evicted from their seats as everyone in the kingdom prepares to look for a new permanent home to conquer. During this time, Seats of Power in your home kingdom cannot be attacked or taken. Allegiances compete by holding as many Seats of Power as possible in any of the new kingdoms, rewarding them with event points. Points earned will not be lost when traveling to another kingdom. In the new kingdoms, Seats of Power will unlock using an accelerated schedule, each day providing better seats to conquer. Points earned during the event will depend on the seat being held by the allegiance. Bonus points are earned if your T1 is on the same kingdom. When the event ends, allegiances and their members will win rewards based on the total number of points earned. The Seat of Power unlock schedule will return to normal at the conclusion of the event.
There will be 2 new kingdoms available to pick from while the event is active, and you can freely travel to any of these kingdoms throughout the event. The event panel will include a "Stake Your Claim" teleport action allowing you to select a kingdom. Once you leave your original kingdom you cannot return as travel is only permitted between the new kingdoms.
It's important for you to know that at the end of the event you will be moved to the kingdom your T1 resides.
If you have not selected a new kingdom by the end of the event, you will be randomly moved to one. If a kingdom is overpopulated at the conclusion of the event, some allegiances will be moved to another kingdom. 

Good luck and thank you for playing Game of Thrones: Conquest!
